definitions.definition: Dwelling, or having an abode, in a place for a continued length of time; residing on one's own estate.
examples: resident in the city or in the country

definitions.definition: Based in a particular place; on hand ; local .
examples: He is our resident computer expert.

definitions.definition: Currently loaded into RAM ; contrasted with virtual memory .
